# ACKO UI Hard Constraints

These rules apply to EVERY React component you generate. No exceptions.

## Typography
- ALL text MUST use `<Typography variant="..." weight="...">`. Never use raw `<h1>`, `<h2>`, `<p>`, `<span>` with inline font styles.
- Never set `fontSize`, `fontWeight`, or `fontFamily` inline on any element.
- The Euclid Circular B font loads globally via `@acko/css` — do NOT set `fontFamily` anywhere in a component.

## Spacing & Colour
- ALL spacing MUST use `var(--space-*)` tokens. Never use hardcoded px values (e.g. `padding: "16px"` ❌).
- ALL colours MUST use semantic tokens: `var(--color-primary)`, `var(--color-text-strong)`, `var(--color-surface)`, etc. Never use hex codes or raw colour names.
- Border radius MUST use `var(--radius-*)` tokens. Never use `borderRadius: "8px"`.

## Icons
- UI icons MUST come from `lucide-react`. Never write inline SVGs for icons.

## Animations
- `transition: all` is BANNED. Always target specific properties: `transition: "opacity 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease"`.
- Always respect `prefers-reduced-motion` — use `useReducedMotion()` from `framer-motion` or a CSS `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` guard.

## Accessibility
- Interactive elements must have `touchAction: "manipulation"`.
- Use `role`, `aria-checked`, `tabIndex`, and `onKeyDown` on custom interactive elements.

